Develop a PHP program to use session variables and start a session.

SOLUTION:
Explanation:
session_start() → Must be called before using any $_SESSION variables.
$_SESSION['username'] → Stores data across multiple pages.
print_r($_SESSION) → Displays all current session values.
The session persists until the user closes the browser or session_destroy() is called.

CODE:
<?php
// Start the session
session_start();

// Check if session variable 'username' is set
if (!isset($_SESSION['username'])) {
    // Assign a value to session variable
    $_SESSION['username'] = "Kanishka";
    $_SESSION['role'] = "Student";
    echo "Session variables are set.<br>";
} else {
    echo "Welcome back, " . $_SESSION['username'] . "!<br>";
    echo "Your role is: " . $_SESSION['role'] . "<br>";
}

// Display all session variables
echo "<pre>";
print_r($_SESSION);
echo "</pre>";
?>

OUTPUT:
Session variables are set.<br><pre>Array
(
    [username] => Kanishka
    [role] => Student
)
</pre>


